The paper deals with the angular resolution of straight-line drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the total angular resolution of graphs, which involves the crossing resolution and can be seen as a graph-theoretic property (cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT). The paper also mentions the NP-hardness of deciding whether a graph has a certain total angular resolution, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.SI).
